As Dat wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/13/2004 at 09:08:16 (Eastern Time),
>[If two triangles have the same altitude, then their areas are 
>proportional to their bases. ]
>is this a theorem? if so, could you please tell me what website 
>provides more detail about this
>
>

This is a well-known theorem, and should be in any geometry text. Or,
just consider the formula for the area of a trianglem, A = bh/2. If h
is the same, A is proportional to b.


